# Section separation

Keep code in clear folders. Do not dump everything in one file or one folder.

```
app/   (or src/orchestrator/)
  components/   # presentational + composed UI (agents/ for orchestrator)
  hooks/        # reusable use* hooks
  types/        # shared types + interfaces
  utils/        # pure helpers (no React)
  context/      # providers + useContext hooks
  index.ts      # barrel re-exports
```

For `src/orchestrator/`, map concerns like this:

```
src/orchestrator/
  types/        # InteractionEvent, OrchestratorTurn, …
  utils/        # llm, debounce, text, deliver
  agents/       # interaction + execution (composed logic)
  bounce/       # inbound debounce
  handoff/      # assign_task + notify bus
  memory/       # conversation history
  prompts/      # system prompt markdown
  index.ts
```

## Rules

- **components** — UI only. No fetch/business logic that belongs in services or hooks.
- **hooks** — shared stateful/logic hooks (`useMarkets`, `useSearch`).
- **types** — shared types. Colocate tiny local types next to the file that owns them.
- **utils** — pure functions. No hooks, no JSX.
- **context** — use React context + `useContext` when prop drilling gets deep (3+ levels) or many siblings need same state. Prefer props for one-level parent → child.

```tsx
// BAD — prop drill through many layers
<Layout user={user}>
  <Sidebar user={user}>
    <Nav user={user} />
  </Sidebar>
</Layout>

// GOOD — context when many consumers need same value
const UserContext = createContext<User | null>(null);
const useUser = () => {
  const user = useContext(UserContext);
  if (!user) throw new Error("useUser requires UserProvider");
  return user;
};
```

Route files (`app/routes/*`) stay thin: load/action + compose components/hooks.

## Services

`app/services/<domain>/` follow same split:

```
app/services/
  index.server.ts       # barrel re-exports (server-only)
  polymarket/
    types.ts
    utils.ts
    gamma.server.ts
    index.server.ts
  markets/
    types.ts
    utils.ts
    shop-market.server.ts
    index.server.ts
```

## Barrel `index.ts` / `index.server.ts`

Each shared folder gets a barrel with one-liner re-exports. Server-only modules use `index.server.ts`. Import the explicit file path (directory imports break under React Router `rootDirs`):

```ts
// GOOD
import { searchMarkets, pickShopMarket } from "../services/index.server";

// BAD — fails typecheck with rootDirs
import { searchMarkets } from "../services";
```
